This paper deals with the problem of data integration, which is a common topic in the database community (cs.DB). The use of possible-worlds and probability distributions suggests a focus on probabilistic reasoning and uncertainty, which are key topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The efficient integration of data also involves algorithmic and computational aspects, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the problem of determining the probability distribution of the integration result involves information theory and probability theory (cs.IT).
